The Optimized Direct Method maintains a reaction dependency graph. Since each reaction fired only affects a few other reactions, the dependency graph significantly reduces the cost of updating propensities. Instead of computing the total sum of propensities aR at each update step, it only computes the sum incrementally. The search for the reaction to be fired, however, is a simple linear search. Since in general bio-chemical systems only a small fraction of the reactions are regularly fired, sorting the list of propensities by magnitude significantly reduces the cost of the linear search.

